ndrinos</b>, a habitational name from the Kassandra peninsula of Chalkidiki), and various patronymics from the personal name <i>Charalampos</i> (see   Charos  ). In North America, the surname <i>Harris</i> may possibly also originate from a transferred use of the Greek personal (given) name <i>Charis</i> or <i>Harris</i> (shortened forms of <i>Charalampos</i>) as a surname (i.e. as a replacement of the original surname).","Americanized form of various like-sounding Jewish surnames."]}]},{"name":"Lady","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>lavedi</i>, <i>levedi</i>, <i>ladi</i> ‘lady, female head of a household, woman, wife’ (Old English <i>hlǣfdige</i>). As a man's name it may have been used in mockery, or be short for occupational names such as <b>Ladyman</b>.","Polish: variant of   Lada  .","Hungarian (<b>Ládi</b>): habitational name for someone from Lád in Borsod County or Lad in Somogy County."],"variants":[{"name":"Lada","meanings":["‘tendril’ or ‘creeper’, often used in metaphors describing the slender curvature of eyebrows, arms, hair, swords, lightning, and women's bodies."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Herries was born in 1358, in Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland, her father, Sir Herries, was 28 and her mother, Lady Herries, was 24. She had at least 1 son with David Currie. She died in 1444, in her hometown, at the age of 86."},"et":{"1358–1444":"1358–1444","1358–1378":"1358–1378","1378–1444":"1378–1444","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1334–Female":"1334–Surnud","1358":"1358","1378":"1378","1444":"1444","1334":"1334","1330":"1330","Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1358–1444":"1358–1444","1358–1378":"1358–1378","1378–1444":"1378–1444","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1334–Female":"1334–Kuollut","1358":"1358","1378":"1378","1444":"1444","1334":"1334","1330":"1330","Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotla